Kitaev arXiv:2405.02434 @ refs/kitaev-2405.02434/approximate_algebras.tex:638-642. For a Banach space calA, the bounded linear operators on calA with the operator norm ||w||=sup_{||Z||<=1}||w(Z)|| form a (unital) Banach algebra. Instantiated here at calA=R^n with ||.||_inf, giving M_n(R) (=End(R^n)) a unital Banach algebra under the induced operator norm. CAVEAT: the generic sup-definition + 'bounded linear operators form a Banach algebra' ARE byte-stated; the M_n(R) max-row-ell^1 CLOSED FORM ||A||=max_i sum_j|A_ij| is NOT byte-stated in any present ref (exhaustive grep=0 hits) and is DERIVED inline in node 1.1 (EXTRACTION-LEVEL flag, established lem-P-properties node 1.1.2 pattern). VERBATIM: "Since $\calA$ is a Banach space, linear operators on it have a standard norm,
\begin{equation}
\|w\|=\sup_{\|Z\|\le 1}\|w(Z)\|,\qquad w\colon \calA\to\calA,
\end{equation}
and bounded linear operators form a Banach algebra."
